According to the 2020 "ACS 5-Year Estimates Data Profiles", 41.0% of the township's population spoke only [[American English|English]], while 51.6 spoke an "other [than Spanish] Indo-European language"<ref name=lastcensus/> (mostly being [[Pennsylvania German]]/[[German language|German]]).

